sentences: Yoko Maekawa (前川 陽子, Maekawa Yōko) is a Japanese singer best known for various anime songs, particularly the opening for Cutie Honey.
She rerecorded the openings for Cutie Honey and Majokko Megu-chan, titling them "21st century" versions, in 2008.
The Cutie Honey opening was originally intended to be performed by Linda Yamamoto.
Along With the Wind (Pyunpyun Maru ED, 1967)
Magic of Mambo (Sally the Witch ED, 1967)
Night Fog of Honey (Cutie Honey ED, 1973)
Megu is All Alone (Majokko Megu-chan ED, 1974)
Pearl Colored Waltz (Maya the Bee ED 2, 1975)
